<TITLE> Khetmajur Samity demands rural allocation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 23 (bdnews24.com)  Khetmajur Samity, farmers wing of the Communist Party of Bangladesh, on Saturday made a seven-point demand. The demands included that the government post rural project allocation of the upcoming budget on its website and launch a 100-day job generation programme. The Khetmajur Samity placed the demands at a press conference at the CPB office in Purana Paltan on Saturday. The other demands include generating permanent employment for farm labourers in the upcoming budget and 40 percent allocation for development budget. They also demanded that the government export unemployed youths abroad as human resource after giving them vocational training. They demanded that upazila and union councils be made effective, interference of MPs be stopped and distribution of Khas land among the landless through a land commission. In the written statement, the organisation's secretary Anwar Hossain said, "We believe that millions of people have gone under the poverty line. We demand separate allocation for the rural population for the improvement of their lot." The press conference was also attended among others by the organisation's president Shamsuzzaman Selim. bdne
